data.title: Trinidad Province
data.meta_description: The Province of Trinidad (1525–1802) was a province of the Spanish Empire which was created in 1525.
data.text:
The Province of Trinidad (1525–1802) was a province of the Spanish Empire which was created in 1525.

From 1591 to 1731 it was merged with Guayana Province, as Trinidad-Guayana Province. It was lost to the British in 1797, a loss recognised by the Treaty of Amiens in 1802.
